The awards, presented by WAN-IFRA, the World association of newspapers and news publishers, recognise publishers which have adopted digital media and mobile strategies as part of their total product offering to meet the major changes in how people consume news and information today. The categories include: Best News Website; Best in Lifestyle, Sports or Entertainment Website; Best Use of Online Video; Best Data Visualisation; Best News Mobile Service; Best Lifestyle, Sports or Entertainment Mobile Services; Best Innovation New Product; Best in Social Media Engagement; Best Digital Advertising Campaign; Best innovation to engage Youth Audiences. Enter here. The awards will take place in Nairobi, Kenya on 29 November 2017.